Pre-Game Insights: Coach Walid Regragui confirmed his players' readiness for tonight’s game, including new additions.
Morocco has shown strong form in the ongoing qualifiers, securing key victories over Gabon and Lesotho.
Morocco is the clear favorite to win the game, but the Central African Republic will be determined to put up a fight.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game will kick off this evening at 8:00 pm GMT+1 at the Stade d’Honneur in Oujda.
The match will be broadcast live on Moroccan sports networks, including Arryadia.
For those unable to watch on TV, the match will be available via streaming platforms, with possible coverage on BeIN Sports Connect or FuboTV, depending on your region.
Others: Morocco is expected to score 13 goals and concede only three in their last five matches.
Key players Hakim Ziyech, Noussair Mazraoui, and Brahim Diaz are unavailable due to injuries.
New talents like Youssef Belammari and Ismael Saibari will have the chance to shine.
